column1: Which team will win the 2018 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Championship?
column11: The 2018 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Championship will be held on 2 April 2018 (NCAA). The names of the regional champions will be substituted in once known. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: Michigan has the easiest entry 7:1 via loya. Loya has won all its games by 1-2 points.

Loyla-Chicago are the clear underdogs, so their region is assigned the lowest % (https://www.cbssports.com/college-basketball/news/2018-ncaa-tournament-final-four-odds-picks-advanced-computer-model-says-fade-loyola-chicago/). Consequently, this increases Michigan's chances by guaranteeing them a place in the final.

The winner of the East (#1 Villanova) vs Midwest (#1 Kansas) will almost certainly win the tournament, against either #11 Loyola-Chi or #3 Michigan. Villanova's experience, coaching, and fundamental skills suggest it would win out well more than half the time.
A tentative initial forecast, presuming the strongest teams are distributed equally across the regions. Will update after research.
